        <briefdescription>
<para>Computes the base 2^b representation of X, converts a byte string into an array of integers in the range [0, 2^b - 1]. </para>        </briefdescription>
        <detaileddescription>
<para><parameterlist kind="param"><parameteritem>
<parameternamelist>
<parametername>BaseB</parametername>
</parameternamelist>
<parameterdescription>
<para>Output array to store the base 2^b representation. </para></parameterdescription>
</parameteritem>
<parameteritem>
<parameternamelist>
<parametername>X</parametername>
</parameternamelist>
<parameterdescription>
<para>Input byte string (must have at least (OutLen*b)/8 bytes). </para></parameterdescription>
</parameteritem>
<parameteritem>
<parameternamelist>
<parametername>b</parametername>
</parameternamelist>
<parameterdescription>
<para>The base parameter (number of bits per output element). </para></parameterdescription>
</parameteritem>
<parameteritem>
<parameternamelist>
<parametername>OutLen</parametername>
</parameternamelist>
<parameterdescription>
<para>The number of output elements to generate. </para></parameterdescription>
</parameteritem>
</parameterlist>
</para>        </detaileddescription>
        <inbodydescription>
<para><itemizedlist>
<listitem><para>Step 4: for out from 0 to out_len - 1 do</para></listitem><listitem><para>Step 5: while bits &lt; b do</para></listitem><listitem><para>Step 6: total &lt;- (total &lt;&lt; 8) + X[in]</para></listitem><listitem><para>Step 7: in &lt;- in+1</para></listitem><listitem><para>Step 8: bits &lt;- bits + 8</para></listitem><listitem><para>Step 9: end while</para></listitem><listitem><para>Step 10: bits &lt;- bits - b</para></listitem><listitem><para>Step 11: baseb[out] &lt;- (total &gt;&gt; bits) mod 2^b</para></listitem><listitem><para>Step 12: end for</para></listitem><listitem><para>Step 13: return baseb (implicit through BaseB output parameter) </para></listitem></itemizedlist>
</para>        </inbodydescription>
